                    <span>Anyone dealing with mobile and wireless computing needs to have this book on their desk. It is a great reference, providing a comprehensive and non-biased overview of the different facets of the mobile and wireless space. <p>It is uniquely written in such a way that it can be read, understood and enjoyed by a wide variety of readers. From any IT sales staff needing to understand the mobile and wireless market space, the latest technologies, competing technologies and buzzwords, to the project managers needing to implement real life mobile solutions, to the hard-core techies looking for a introduction into new technology, this book will apply...<p>It is appropriately titled and provides exactly what is says. <p>Read this if you want a competitive advantage in the mobile and wireless space.</span>
                  
              
